83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4043
Introduced and printed pursuant to House Rule 12.00. Presession filed (at the request of House Interim Committee
on Judiciary for Representative Jason Kropf)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: The Act lets the State Treasurer issue bonds to pay to expand or renovate courthouses.
(Flesch Readability Score: 61.8).
Authorizes the State Treasurer to issue Article XI-Q general obligation bonds to finance reno-
vation or expansion of courthouses.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to courts; amending ORS 1.181, 1.183 and 1.184.
3 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
4 SECTION 1. ORS 1.181 is amended to read:
5 1.181. (1) Out of the amount specified in section 1 (6), chapter 705, Oregon Laws 2013, the State
6 Treasurer may issue Article XI-Q bonds in an amount not to exceed $19 million of net proceeds for
7 the purposes specified in subsection [(3)] (6) of this section, plus an amount estimated by the State
8 Treasurer to pay estimated bond-related costs.
9 (2)[(a)] Bonds may not be issued pursuant to this section or section 10, chapter 685, Oregon
10 Laws 2015, unless[:] a courthouse project meets the requirements of subsection (3) or (4) of
11 this section.
12 (3) Bonds may be issued pursuant to this section or section 10, chapter 685, Oregon Laws
13 2015, if:
14 [(A)] (a) The Chief Justice of the Supreme Court has determined that:
15 [(i)] (A) The courthouse with respect to which the bonds will be issued has significant structural
16 defects, including seismic defects, that present actual or potential threats to human health and
17 safety;
18 [(ii)] (B) Replacing the courthouse, whether by acquiring and remodeling or repairing an exist-
19 ing building or by constructing a new building, is more cost-effective than remodeling or repairing
20 the courthouse; and
21 [(iii)] (C) Replacing the courthouse creates an opportunity for colocation of the court with other
22 state offices; and
23 [(B)] (b) The Oregon Department of Administrative Services has approved the project for which
24 the bonds will be issued.
25 (4) Bonds may be issued pursuant to this section or section 10, chapter 685, Oregon Laws
26 2015, if:
27 (a) The Chief Justice of the Supreme Court has determined that:
28 (A) Renovating or expanding the court space in the courthouse, by remodeling or re-
29 pairing the existing courthouse space or by constructing an addition to the existing court-
